msgid ""
"\n"
"HBAC Service Groups\n"
"\n"
"HBAC service groups can contain any number of individual services,\n"
"or \"members\". Every group must have a description.\n"
"\n"
"EXAMPLES:\n"
"\n"
" Add a new HBAC service group:\n"
"   ipa hbacsvcgroup-add --desc=\"login services\" login\n"
"\n"
" Add members to an HBAC service group:\n"
"   ipa hbacsvcgroup-add-member --hbacsvcs=sshd,login login\n"
"\n"
" Display information about a named group:\n"
"   ipa hbacsvcgroup-show login\n"
"\n"
" Add a new group to the \"login\" group:\n"
"   ipa hbacsvcgroup-add --desc=\"switch users\" login\n"
"   ipa hbacsvcgroup-add-member --hbacsvcs=su,su-l login\n"
"\n"
" Delete an HBAC service group:\n"
"   ipa hbacsvcgroup-del login\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"HBAC-tjänstegrupper\n"
"\n"
"HBAC-tjänstegrupper kan innehålla valfritt antal enskilda tjänster,\n"
"eller ”medlemmar”. Varje grupp måste ha en beskrivning.\n"
"\n"
"EXEMPEL:\n"
"\n"
"Lägg till en ny HBAC-tjänstegrupp:\n"
"ipa hbacsvcgroup-add --desc=\"login services\" login Lägg\n"
"\n"
"till medlemmar i en HBAC-tjänstegrupp:\n"
"ipa hbacsvcgroup-add-member --hbacsvcs=sshd,login Visa\n"
"\n"
"information om en namngiven grupp: ipa\n"
"hbacsvcgroup-show login Lägg\n"
"\n"
"till en ny grupp till gruppen \"login\":\n"
"ipa hbacsvcgroup-add --desc=\"switch users\" login ipa\n"
"hbacsvcgroup-add-member --hbacsvcs=su,su-l login Ta bort\n"
"\n"
"en HBAC-tjänstegrupp: ipa\n"
"hbacsvcgroup-del login\n"

msgid ""
"\n"
"Simulate use of Host-based access controls\n"
"\n"
"HBAC rules control who can access what services on what hosts and from "
"where.\n"
"You can use HBAC to control which users or groups can access a service,\n"
"or group of services, on a target host.\n"
"\n"
"Since applying HBAC rules implies use of a production environment,\n"
"this plugin aims to provide simulation of HBAC rules evaluation without\n"
"having access to the production environment.\n"
"\n"
" Test user coming to a service on a named host against\n"
" existing enabled rules.\n"
"\n"
" ipa hbactest --user= --host= --service=\n"
"              [--rules=rules-list] [--nodetail] [--enabled] [--disabled]\n"
"              [--srchost= ] [--sizelimit= ]\n"
"\n"
" --user, --host, and --service are mandatory, others are optional.\n"
"\n"
" If --rules is specified simulate enabling of the specified rules and test\n"
" the login of the user using only these rules.\n"
"\n"
" If --enabled is specified, all enabled HBAC rules will be added to "
"simulation\n"
"\n"
" If --disabled is specified, all disabled HBAC rules will be added to "
"simulation\n"
"\n"
" If --nodetail is specified, do not return information about rules matched/"
"not matched.\n"
"\n"
" If both --rules and --enabled are specified, apply simulation to --rules "
"_and_\n"
" all IPA enabled rules.\n"
"\n"
" If no --rules specified, simulation is run against all IPA enabled rules.\n"
" By default there is a IPA-wide limit to number of entries fetched, you can "
"change it\n"
" with --sizelimit option.\n"
"\n"
" If --srchost is specified, it will be ignored. It is left because of "
"compatibility reasons only.\n"
"\n"
"EXAMPLES:\n"
"\n"
"    1. Use all enabled HBAC rules in IPA database to simulate:\n"
"    $ ipa  hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"    Access granted: True\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"      notmatched: my-second-rule\n"
"      notmatched: my-third-rule\n"
"      notmatched: myrule\n"
"      matched: allow_all\n"
"\n"
"    2. Disable detailed summary of how rules were applied:\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd --nodetail\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"    Access granted: True\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"\n"
"    3. Test explicitly specified HBAC rules:\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd           --rules=my-"
"second-rule,myrule\n"
"    ---------------------\n"
"    Access granted: False\n"
"    ---------------------\n"
"      notmatched: my-second-rule\n"
"      notmatched: myrule\n"
"\n"
"    4. Use all enabled HBAC rules in IPA database + explicitly specified "
"rules:\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd           --rules=my-"
"second-rule,myrule --enabled\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"    Access granted: True\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"      notmatched: my-second-rule\n"
"      notmatched: my-third-rule\n"
"      notmatched: myrule\n"
"      matched: allow_all\n"
"\n"
"    5. Test all disabled HBAC rules in IPA database:\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd --disabled\n"
"    ---------------------\n"
"    Access granted: False\n"
"    ---------------------\n"
"      notmatched: new-rule\n"
"\n"
"    6. Test all disabled HBAC rules in IPA database + explicitly specified "
"rules:\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd           --rules=my-"
"second-rule,myrule --disabled\n"
"    ---------------------\n"
"    Access granted: False\n"
"    ---------------------\n"
"      notmatched: my-second-rule\n"
"      notmatched: my-third-rule\n"
"      notmatched: myrule\n"
"\n"
"    7. Test all (enabled and disabled) HBAC rules in IPA database:\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd           --enabled "
"--disabled\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"    Access granted: True\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"      notmatched: my-second-rule\n"
"      notmatched: my-third-rule\n"
"      notmatched: myrule\n"
"      notmatched: new-rule\n"
"      matched: allow_all\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Simulera användning av värdbaserade\n"
"\n"
"åtkomstkontroller HBAC-regler styr vem som kan komma åt vilka tjänster på\n"
"vilka värdar och från var. Du kan använda HBAC för att styra vilka\n"
"användare eller grupper som kan komma\n"
"\n"
"åt en tjänst eller en grupp av tjänster på en målvärd. Eftersom\n"
"tillämpning av HBAC-regler innebär användning av en produktionsmiljö\n"
"syftar detta insticksmodul till att simulera\n"
"\n"
"utvärdering av HBAC-regler utan att ha åtkomst till\n"
"produktionsmiljön. Testa\n"
"\n"
"användare som kommer till en tjänst på\n"
"en namngiven värd mot befintliga aktiverade regler. ipa hbactest --user=\n"
"--host= --service= [--rules=rules-list]\n"
"\n"
"[--nodetail] [--enabled] [--disabled] [--srchost= ] [--sizelimit=\n"
"\n"
"] --user, --host och --service är obligatoriska, övriga är valfria. Om\n"
"--rules anges simuleras aktivering av de angivna\n"
"\n"
"reglerna och användarens inloggning testas med endast dessa regler. Om --"
"enabled\n"
"\n"
"anges kommer alla aktiverade HBAC-regler att läggas till i simuleringen. Om\n"
"\n"
"--disabled anges kommer alla inaktiverade HBAC-regler att läggas till i "
"simuleringen.\n"
"\n"
"Om --nodetail anges ska information om matchade/icke matchade regler inte\n"
"returneras. Om både\n"
"\n"
"--rules och --enabled anges ska simuleringen tillämpas på --rules _och_\n"
"alla aktiverade IPA-regler. Om ingen --rules anges körs simuleringen mot "
"alla\n"
"IPA-aktiverade regler. Som\n"
"\n"
"standard finns det en IPA-omfattande gräns för antalet hämtade poster, som "
"du kan ändra med\n"
"\n"
"alternativet\n"
"\n"
"--sizelimit. Om --srchost anges ignoreras det. Det finns kvar\n"
"endast av kompatibilitetsskäl. EXEMPEL: 1. Använd alla\n"
"aktiverade HBAC-regler i\n"
"IPA-databasen för att\n"
"simulera: $ ipa hbactest\n"
"--user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd\n"
"-------------------- Åtkomst\n"
"beviljad: Sant\n"
"--------------------\n"
"\n"
"notmatched: my-second-rule notmatched: my-third-rule\n"
"notmatched: myrule matched: allow_all 2. Inaktivera detaljerad\n"
"sammanfattning av hur\n"
"reglerna tillämpades: $\n"
"ipa hbactest --user=a1a\n"
"\n"
"--host=bar --service=sshd --nodetail\n"
"-------------------- Åtkomst beviljad: Sant -------------------- 3. Testa "
"uttryckligen angivna\n"
"HBAC-regler: $ ipa hbactest\n"
"--user=a1a --host=bar\n"
"--service=sshd\n"
"--rules=my-second-rule,myrule\n"
"---------------------\n"
"\n"
"Åtkomst beviljad: False --------------------- notmatched: my-second-rule\n"
"notmatched: myrule 4. Använd alla aktiverade HBAC-regler i IPA-databasen + "
"uttryckligen angivna regler:\n"
"$ ipa hbactest --user=a1a\n"
"--host=bar --service=sshd\n"
"--rules=my-second-rule,myrule\n"
"--enabled --------------------\n"
"Tillgång beviljad: Sant\n"
"--------------------\n"
"notmatched: min-andra-regel\n"
"\n"
"notmatched: min-tredje-regel notmatched: minregel\n"
"matched: allow_all 5. Testa alla inaktiverade HBAC-regler i\n"
"IPA-databasen: $ ipa\n"
"hbactest --user=a1a\n"
"--host=bar --service=sshd\n"
"--disabled ---------------------\n"
"\n"
"Tillgång beviljad: False --------------------- notmatched: new-rule 6. Testa "
"alla\n"
"inaktiverade HBAC-regler i IPA-databasen + uttryckligen angivna regler: $ "
"ipa hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar\n"
"--service=sshd\n"
"--rules=my-second-rule,myrule\n"
"--disabled ---------------------\n"
"Åtkomst beviljad: False\n"
"--------------------- notmatched:\n"
"my-second-rule notmatched:\n"
"\n"
"my-third-rule notmatched: myrule 7. Testa alla (aktiverade och\n"
"inaktiverade) HBAC-regler i IPA-databasen: $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a --"
"host=bar\n"
"--service=sshd --enabled\n"
"--disabled --------------------\n"
"Tillgång beviljad: Sant\n"
"-------------------- notmatched:\n"
"min-andra-regel notmatched:\n"
"min-tredje-regel notmatched:\n"
"minregel notmatched: ny-regel\n"
"matched: allow_all\n"

#: ipaserver/plugins/hbactest.py:278
msgid "Source host"
msgstr "Källvärd"

msgid ""
"\n"
"Hosts/Machines\n"
"\n"
"A host represents a machine. It can be used in a number of contexts:\n"
"- service entries are associated with a host\n"
"- a host stores the host/ service principal\n"
"- a host can be used in Host-based Access Control (HBAC) rules\n"
"- every enrolled client generates a host entry\n"
"\n"
"ENROLLMENT:\n"
"\n"
"There are three enrollment scenarios when enrolling a new client:\n"
"\n"
"1. You are enrolling as a full administrator. The host entry may exist\n"
"   or not. A full administrator is a member of the hostadmin role\n"
"   or the admins group.\n"
"2. You are enrolling as a limited administrator. The host must already\n"
"   exist. A limited administrator is a member a role with the\n"
"   Host Enrollment privilege.\n"
"3. The host has been created with a one-time password.\n"
"\n"
"A host can only be enrolled once. If a client has enrolled and needs to\n"
"be re-enrolled, the host entry must be removed and re-created. Note that\n"
"re-creating the host entry will result in all services for the host being\n"
"removed, and all SSL certificates associated with those services being\n"
"revoked.\n"
"\n"
"A host can optionally store information such as where it is located,\n"
"the OS that it runs, etc.\n"
"\n"
"EXAMPLES:\n"
"\n"
" Add a new host:\n"
"   ipa host-add --location=\"3rd floor lab\" --locality=Dallas test.example."
"com\n"
"\n"
" Delete a host:\n"
"   ipa host-del test.example.com\n"
"\n"
" Add a new host with a one-time password:\n"
"   ipa host-add --os='Fedora 12' --password=Secret123 test.example.com\n"
"\n"
" Add a new host with a random one-time password:\n"
"   ipa host-add --os='Fedora 12' --random test.example.com\n"
"\n"
" Modify information about a host:\n"
"   ipa host-mod --os='Fedora 12' test.example.com\n"
"\n"
" Remove SSH public keys of a host and update DNS to reflect this change:\n"
"   ipa host-mod --sshpubkey= --updatedns test.example.com\n"
"\n"
" Disable the host Kerberos key, SSL certificate and all of its services:\n"
"   ipa host-disable test.example.com\n"
"\n"
" Add a host that can manage this host's keytab and certificate:\n"
"   ipa host-add-managedby --hosts=test2 test\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Värdar/maskiner\n"
"\n"
"En värd representerar en maskin. Den kan användas i flera sammanhang: -\n"
"tjänsteposter är kopplade till en värd - en värd\n"
"lagrar värd-/tjänstprincipalen - en värd kan\n"
"användas i regler för värdbaserad åtkomstkontroll (HBAC) - varje\n"
"registrerad klient genererar en värdpost REGISTRERING:\n"
"\n"
"Det finns tre\n"
"\n"
"registreringsscenarier när du registrerar en ny klient: 1. Du registrerar\n"
"\n"
"dig som fullständig administratör. Värdposteringen kan finnas eller inte.\n"
"En fullständig administratör är medlem i rollen hostadmin eller gruppen\n"
"admins. 2. Du registrerar\n"
"dig som begränsad administratör. Värden måste redan finnas. En begränsad\n"
"administratör är medlem i en roll med behörigheten Host Enrollment.\n"
"3. Värden har skapats med ett\n"
"engångslösenord. En värd kan endast registreras en gång.\n"
"\n"
"Om en klient har registrerats och behöver registreras på nytt måste\n"
"värdposteringen tas bort och skapas på nytt. Observera att om "
"värdposteringen\n"
"skapas på nytt kommer alla tjänster för värden att tas bort och alla SSL-"
"certifikat\n"
"som är associerade med dessa tjänster att återkallas. En värd kan valfritt\n"
"lagra\n"
"\n"
"information såsom var den är belägen, vilket operativsystem den kör etc.\n"
"EXEMPEL: Lägg till en ny\n"
"\n"
"värd: ipa\n"
"\n"
"host-add --location=\"3rd\n"
"floor lab\" --locality=Dallas test.example.com Ta bort en värd: ipa host-"
"del\n"
"\n"
"test.example.com\n"
"Lägg till en ny värd med ett\n"
"\n"
"engångslösenord: ipa host-add --os='Fedora\n"
"12' --password=Secret123 test.example.com Lägg till en ny värd med ett\n"
"\n"
"slumpmässigt engångslösenord: ipa host-add --os='Fedora\n"
"12' --random test.example.com Ändra information om en värd:\n"
"\n"
"ipa host-mod --os='Fedora 12'\n"
"test.example.com Ta bort SSH-publiknycklar för en\n"
"\n"
"värd och uppdatera DNS för att återspegla denna ändring: ipa host-mod\n"
"--sshpubkey= --updatedns test.example.com Inaktivera värdens\n"
"\n"
"Kerberos-nyckel, SSL-certifikat och alla dess tjänster: ipa host-disable\n"
"test.example.com Lägg till en värd som\n"
"\n"
"kan hantera denna värds keytab och certifikat: ipa host-add-managedby\n"
"--hosts=test2 test\n"

msgid ""
"\n"
"Groups of hosts.\n"
"\n"
"Manage groups of hosts. This is useful for applying access control to a\n"
"number of hosts by using Host-based Access Control.\n"
"\n"
"EXAMPLES:\n"
"\n"
" Add a new host group:\n"
"   ipa hostgroup-add --desc=\"Baltimore hosts\" baltimore\n"
"\n"
" Add another new host group:\n"
"   ipa hostgroup-add --desc=\"Maryland hosts\" maryland\n"
"\n"
" Add members to the hostgroup:\n"
"   ipa hostgroup-add-member --hosts=box1,box2,box3 baltimore\n"
"\n"
" Add a hostgroup as a member of another hostgroup:\n"
"   ipa hostgroup-add-member --hostgroups=baltimore maryland\n"
"\n"
" Remove a host from the hostgroup:\n"
"   ipa hostgroup-remove-member --hosts=box2 baltimore\n"
"\n"
" Display a host group:\n"
"   ipa hostgroup-show baltimore\n"
"\n"
" Delete a hostgroup:\n"
"   ipa hostgroup-del baltimore\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Grupper av värdar.\n"
"\n"
"Hantera grupper av värdar. Detta är användbart för att tillämpa "
"åtkomstkontroll\n"
"på ett antal värdar med hjälp av värdbaserad\n"
"\n"
"åtkomstkontroll.\n"
"\n"
"EXEMPEL: Lägg till en\n"
"ny värdgrupp: ipa hostgroup-add --desc=\"Baltimore hosts\"\n"
"\n"
"baltimore Lägg till en ny\n"
"värdgrupp: ipa hostgroup-add --desc=\"Maryland hosts\"\n"
"\n"
"maryland Lägg till medlemmar till\n"
"värdgruppen: ipa hostgroup-add-member --hosts=box1,box2,box3\n"
"\n"
"baltimore Lägg till en värdgrupp som medlem i en annan\n"
"värdgrupp: ipa hostgroup-add-member --hostgroups=baltimore\n"
"\n"
"maryland Ta bort en värd från\n"
"värdgruppen: ipa hostgroup-remove-member --hosts=box2\n"
"\n"
"baltimore Visa en\n"
"värdgrupp: ipa hostgroup-show\n"
"\n"
"baltimore Ta bort en\n"
"värdgrupp: ipa hostgroup-del\n"
"baltimore\n"

msgid ""
"Comma-separated list of objectclasses used to search for user entries in DS"
msgstr ""
"Kommaseparerad lista över objektklasser som används för att söka efter "
"användarposter i DS"

msgid ""
"Comma-separated list of objectclasses used to search for group entries in DS"
msgstr ""
"Kommaseparerad lista över objektklasser som används för att söka efter "
"gruppposter i DS"

msgid ""
"Comma-separated list of objectclasses to be ignored for user entries in DS"
msgstr ""
"Kommaseparerad lista över objektklasser som ska ignoreras för användarposter "
"i DS"

msgid "Comma-separated list of attributes to be ignored for user entries in DS"
msgstr ""
"Kommaseparerad lista över attribut som ska ignoreras för användarinmatningar "
"i DS"

msgid ""
"Comma-separated list of objectclasses to be ignored for group entries in DS"
msgstr ""
"Kommaseparerad lista över objektklasser som ska ignoreras för gruppposter i "
"DS"

msgid ""
"Comma-separated list of attributes to be ignored for group entries in DS"
msgstr ""
"Kommaseparerad lista över attribut som ska ignoreras för gruppposter i DS"

msgid "comma-separated list of groups to exclude from migration"
msgstr "kommaseparerad lista över grupper som ska undantas från migreringen"

msgid "comma-separated list of users to exclude from migration"
msgstr "kommaseparerad lista över användare som ska undantas från migreringen"

msgid ""
"\n"
"Netgroups\n"
"\n"
"A netgroup is a group used for permission checking. It can contain both\n"
"user and host values.\n"
"\n"
"EXAMPLES:\n"
"\n"
" Add a new netgroup:\n"
"   ipa netgroup-add --desc=\"NFS admins\" admins\n"
"\n"
" Add members to the netgroup:\n"
"   ipa netgroup-add-member --users=tuser1,tuser2 admins\n"
"\n"
" Remove a member from the netgroup:\n"
"   ipa netgroup-remove-member --users=tuser2 admins\n"
"\n"
" Display information about a netgroup:\n"
"   ipa netgroup-show admins\n"
"\n"
" Delete a netgroup:\n"
"   ipa netgroup-del admins\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Nätgrupper\n"
"\n"
"En nätgrupp är en grupp som används för behörighetskontroll. Den kan "
"innehålla\n"
"både användar- och\n"
"\n"
"värdvärden.\n"
"\n"
"EXEMPEL: Lägg till en\n"
"ny nätgrupp: ipa netgroup-add --desc=\"NFS-administratörer\"\n"
"\n"
"admins Lägg till medlemmar i\n"
"nätgruppen: ipa netgroup-add-member --users=tuser1,tuser2\n"
"\n"
"admins Ta bort en medlem från nätgruppen:\n"
"ipa netgroup-remove-member --users=tuser2 admins Visa\n"
"\n"
"information om en nätgrupp: ipa netgroup-show\n"
"admins Ta bort en nätgrupp:\n"
"\n"
"ipa netgroup-del adm\n"
"ins\n"

msgid "comma-separated list of netgroups to add"
msgstr "kommaseparerad lista över nätgrupper som ska läggas till"

msgid "comma-separated list of netgroups to remove"
msgstr "kommaseparerad lista över nätgrupper som ska tas bort"

msgid ""
"\n"
"Permissions\n"
"\n"
"A permission enables fine-grained delegation of rights. A permission is\n"
"a human-readable form of a 389-ds Access Control Rule, or instruction "
"(ACI).\n"
"A permission grants the right to perform a specific task such as adding a\n"
"user, modifying a group, etc.\n"
"\n"
"A permission may not contain other permissions.\n"
"\n"
"* A permission grants access to read, write, add or delete.\n"
"* A privilege combines similar permissions (for example all the permissions\n"
"  needed to add a user).\n"
"* A role grants a set of privileges to users, groups, hosts or hostgroups.\n"
"\n"
"A permission is made up of a number of different parts:\n"
"\n"
"1. The name of the permission.\n"
"2. The target of the permission.\n"
"3. The rights granted by the permission.\n"
"\n"
"Rights define what operations are allowed, and may be one or more\n"
"of the following:\n"
"1. write - write one or more attributes\n"
"2. read - read one or more attributes\n"
"3. add - add a new entry to the tree\n"
"4. delete - delete an existing entry\n"
"5. all - all permissions are granted\n"
"\n"
"Read permission is granted for most attributes by default so the read\n"
"permission is not expected to be used very often.\n"
"\n"
"Note the distinction between attributes and entries. The permissions are\n"
"independent, so being able to add a user does not mean that the user will\n"
"be editable.\n"
"\n"
"There are a number of allowed targets:\n"
"1. type: a type of object (user, group, etc).\n"
"2. memberof: a member of a group or hostgroup\n"
"3. filter: an LDAP filter\n"
"4. subtree: an LDAP filter specifying part of the LDAP DIT. This is a\n"
"   super-set of the \"type\" target.\n"
"5. targetgroup: grant access to modify a specific group (such as granting\n"
"   the rights to manage group membership)\n"
"\n"
"EXAMPLES:\n"
"\n"
" Add a permission that grants the creation of users:\n"
"   ipa permission-add --type=user --permissions=add \"Add Users\"\n"
"\n"
" Add a permission that grants the ability to manage group membership:\n"
"   ipa permission-add --attrs=member --permissions=write --type=group "
"\"Manage Group Members\"\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Behörigheter\n"
"\n"
"En behörighet möjliggör detaljerad delegering av rättigheter. En behörighet\n"
"är en läsbar form av en 389-ds Access Control Rule, eller instruktion (ACI). "
"En\n"
"behörighet ger rätt att utföra en specifik uppgift, såsom att lägga till en\n"
"användare, ändra en grupp etc.\n"
"\n"
"En behörighet får inte innehålla andra behörigheter.\n"
"\n"
"* En behörighet ger åtkomst till läsning, skrivning, tillägg\n"
"eller radering. * En behörighet kombinerar liknande behörigheter (till "
"exempel\n"
"alla behörigheter som behövs\n"
"för att lägga till en användare). * En roll ger en uppsättning behörigheter "
"till\n"
"\n"
"användare, grupper, värdar eller värdgrupper. En behörighet\n"
"\n"
"består av ett antal olika delar:\n"
"1. Namnet på behörigheten. 2. Målet\n"
"för behörigheten. 3. De rättigheter som\n"
"\n"
"behörigheten ger. Rättigheter definierar vilka åtgärder som är tillåtna\n"
"och kan vara en eller\n"
"flera av följande: 1. skriva – skriva ett\n"
"eller flera attribut 2. läsa – läsa ett\n"
"eller flera attribut 3. lägga till –\n"
"lägga till en ny post i trädet 4. ta\n"
"bort – ta bort en befintlig post 5. alla\n"
"\n"
"– alla behörigheter beviljas Läsbehörighet beviljas för de flesta attribut\n"
"som standard, så läsbehörigheten förväntas inte användas\n"
"\n"
"särskilt ofta. Observera skillnaden mellan attribut och poster. "
"Behörigheterna\n"
"är oberoende, så att kunna lägga till en användare betyder inte att "
"användaren\n"
"kan redigeras.\n"
"\n"
"Det finns ett antal tillåtna mål: 1. typ:\n"
"en typ av objekt (användare, grupp etc.). 2.\n"
"memberof: en medlem i en grupp eller värdgrupp\n"
"3. filter: ett LDAP-filter\n"
"4. subtree: ett LDAP-filter som specificerar en del av LDAP DIT. Detta är\n"
"en superset av målet \"typ\". 5.\n"
"targetgroup: bevilja åtkomst för att ändra en specifik grupp (t.ex. bevilja\n"
"rättigheter att hantera gruppmedlemskap)\n"
"\n"
"EXEMPEL:\n"
"\n"
"Lägg till en behörighet som ger rätt att skapa användare:\n"
"ipa permission-add --type=user --permissions=add \"Add Users\" Lägg\n"
"\n"
"till en behörighet som ger rätt att hantera gruppmedlemskap: ipa permission-"
"add\n"
"--attrs=member --permissions=write --type=group \"Manage Group Members\"\n"

msgid ""
