#: ipaserver/plugins/certprofile.py:21
msgid ""
"\n"
"Manage Certificate Profiles\n"
"\n"
"Certificate Profiles are used by Certificate Authority (CA) in the signing "
"of\n"
"certificates to determine if a Certificate Signing Request (CSR) is "
"acceptable,\n"
"and if so what features and extensions will be present on the certificate.\n"
"\n"
"The Certificate Profile format is the property-list format understood by "
"the\n"
"Dogtag or Red Hat Certificate System CA.\n"
"\n"
"PROFILE ID SYNTAX:\n"
"\n"
"A Profile ID is a string without spaces or punctuation starting with a "
"letter\n"
"and followed by a sequence of letters, digits or underscore (\"_\").\n"
"\n"
"EXAMPLES:\n"
"\n"
"  Import a profile that will not store issued certificates:\n"
"    ipa certprofile-import ShortLivedUserCert \\\n"
"      --file UserCert.profile --desc \"User Certificates\" \\\n"
"      --store=false\n"
"\n"
"  Delete a certificate profile:\n"
"    ipa certprofile-del ShortLivedUserCert\n"
"\n"
"  Show information about a profile:\n"
"    ipa certprofile-show ShortLivedUserCert\n"
"\n"
"  Save profile configuration to a file:\n"
"    ipa certprofile-show caIPAserviceCert --out caIPAserviceCert.cfg\n"
"\n"
"  Search for profiles that do not store certificates:\n"
"    ipa certprofile-find --store=false\n"
"\n"
"PROFILE CONFIGURATION FORMAT:\n"
"\n"
"The profile configuration format is the raw property-list format\n"
"used by Dogtag Certificate System.  The XML format is not supported.\n"
"\n"
"The following restrictions apply to profiles managed by IPA:\n"
"\n"
"- When importing a profile the \"profileId\" field, if present, must\n"
"  match the ID given on the command line.\n"
"\n"
"- The \"classId\" field must be set to \"caEnrollImpl\"\n"
"\n"
"- The \"auth.instance_id\" field must be set to \"raCertAuth\"\n"
"\n"
"- The \"certReqInputImpl\" input class and \"certOutputImpl\" output\n"
"  class must be used.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Hantera certifikatprofiler\n"
"\n"
"Certifikatprofiler används av certifikatutfärdare (CA) vid signering av\n"
"certifikat för att avgöra om en certifikatsigneringsbegäran (CSR) är "
"acceptabel\n"
"och, i så fall, vilka funktioner och tillägg som ska finnas på "
"certifikatet.\n"
"\n"
"Certifikatprofilformatet är det egenskapslistaformat som förstås av Dogtag\n"
"eller Red Hat Certificate System CA.\n"
"\n"
"PROFIL-ID-SYNTAX:\n"
"\n"
"Ett profil-ID är en sträng utan mellanslag eller skiljetecken som börjar "
"med\n"
"en bokstav och följs av en sekvens av bokstäver, siffror eller\n"
"\n"
"understreck\n"
"\n"
"(\"_\"). EXEMPEL: Importera en profil som inte lagrar utfärdade\n"
"certifikat: ipa certprofile-import ShortLivedUserCert\n"
"\\ --file UserCert.profile --desc \"Användarcertifikat\" \\\n"
"--store=false Ta\n"
"\n"
"bort en certifikatprofil: ipa\n"
"certprofile-del ShortLivedUserCert Visa\n"
"\n"
"information om en profil: ipa\n"
"certprofile-show ShortLivedUserCert Spara\n"
"\n"
"profilkonfigurationen i en fil: ipa\n"
"certprofile-show caIPAserviceCert --out caIPAserviceCert.cfg Sök efter\n"
"\n"
"profiler som inte lagrar certifikat: ipa certprofile-find\n"
"--store=false PROFILKONFIGURATIONSFORMAT:\n"
"\n"
"Profilkonfigurationsformatet\n"
"\n"
"är det råa egenskapslistaformat som används av Dogtag Certificate\n"
"System. XML-formatet stöds inte. Följande begränsningar gäller för\n"
"\n"
"profiler som hanteras av IPA: - När du importerar en profil\n"
"\n"
"måste fältet \"profileId\", om det finns, matcha det ID som anges på\n"
"kommandoraden. - Fältet \"classId\" måste\n"
"\n"
"vara inställt på \"caEnrollImpl\" - Fältet \"auth.instance_id\"\n"
"\n"
"måste vara inställt på \"raCertAuth\" - Inmatningsklassen\n"
"\n"
"\"certReqInputImpl\" och utmatningsklassen \"certOutputImpl\" måste\n"
"användas.\n"
"\n"

