#: ipaserver/plugins/hbactest.py:47
msgid ""
"\n"
"Simulate use of Host-based access controls\n"
"\n"
"HBAC rules control who can access what services on what hosts.\n"
"You can use HBAC to control which users or groups can access a service,\n"
"or group of services, on a target host.\n"
"\n"
"Since applying HBAC rules implies use of a production environment,\n"
"this plugin aims to provide simulation of HBAC rules evaluation without\n"
"having access to the production environment.\n"
"\n"
" Test user coming to a service on a named host against\n"
" existing enabled rules.\n"
"\n"
" ipa hbactest --user= --host= --service=\n"
"              [--rules=rules-list] [--nodetail] [--enabled] [--disabled]\n"
"              [--sizelimit= ]\n"
"\n"
" --user, --host, and --service are mandatory, others are optional.\n"
"\n"
" If --rules is specified simulate enabling of the specified rules and test\n"
" the login of the user using only these rules.\n"
"\n"
" If --enabled is specified, all enabled HBAC rules will be added to "
"simulation\n"
"\n"
" If --disabled is specified, all disabled HBAC rules will be added to "
"simulation\n"
"\n"
" If --nodetail is specified, do not return information about rules matched/"
"not matched.\n"
"\n"
" If both --rules and --enabled are specified, apply simulation to --rules "
"_and_\n"
" all IPA enabled rules.\n"
"\n"
" If no --rules specified, simulation is run against all IPA enabled rules.\n"
" By default there is a IPA-wide limit to number of entries fetched, you can "
"change it\n"
" with --sizelimit option.\n"
"\n"
"EXAMPLES:\n"
"\n"
"    1. Use all enabled HBAC rules in IPA database to simulate:\n"
"    $ ipa  hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"    Access granted: True\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"      Not matched rules: my-second-rule\n"
"      Not matched rules: my-third-rule\n"
"      Not matched rules: myrule\n"
"      Matched rules: allow_all\n"
"\n"
"    2. Disable detailed summary of how rules were applied:\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd --nodetail\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"    Access granted: True\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"\n"
"    3. Test explicitly specified HBAC rules:\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd \\\\\n"
"          --rules=myrule --rules=my-second-rule\n"
"    ---------------------\n"
"    Access granted: False\n"
"    ---------------------\n"
"      Not matched rules: my-second-rule\n"
"      Not matched rules: myrule\n"
"\n"
"    4. Use all enabled HBAC rules in IPA database + explicitly specified "
"rules:\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd \\\\\n"
"          --rules=myrule --rules=my-second-rule --enabled\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"    Access granted: True\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"      Not matched rules: my-second-rule\n"
"      Not matched rules: my-third-rule\n"
"      Not matched rules: myrule\n"
"      Matched rules: allow_all\n"
"\n"
"    5. Test all disabled HBAC rules in IPA database:\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd --disabled\n"
"    ---------------------\n"
"    Access granted: False\n"
"    ---------------------\n"
"      Not matched rules: new-rule\n"
"\n"
"    6. Test all disabled HBAC rules in IPA database + explicitly specified "
"rules:\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd \\\\\n"
"          --rules=myrule --rules=my-second-rule --disabled\n"
"    ---------------------\n"
"    Access granted: False\n"
"    ---------------------\n"
"      Not matched rules: my-second-rule\n"
"      Not matched rules: my-third-rule\n"
"      Not matched rules: myrule\n"
"\n"
"    7. Test all (enabled and disabled) HBAC rules in IPA database:\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd \\\\\n"
"          --enabled --disabled\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"    Access granted: True\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"      Not matched rules: my-second-rule\n"
"      Not matched rules: my-third-rule\n"
"      Not matched rules: myrule\n"
"      Not matched rules: new-rule\n"
"      Matched rules: allow_all\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"HBACTEST AND TRUSTED DOMAINS\n"
"\n"
"When an external trusted domain is configured in IPA, HBAC rules are also "
"applied\n"
"on users accessing IPA resources from the trusted domain. Trusted domain "
"users and\n"
"groups (and their SIDs) can be then assigned to external groups which can "
"be\n"
"members of POSIX groups in IPA which can be used in HBAC rules and thus "
"allowing\n"
"access to resources protected by the HBAC system.\n"
"\n"
"hbactest plugin is capable of testing access for both local IPA users and "
"users\n"
"from the trusted domains, either by a fully qualified user name or by user "
"SID.\n"
"Such user names need to have a trusted domain specified as a short name\n"
"(DOMAIN\\Administrator) or with a user principal name (UPN), "
"Administrator@ad.test.\n"
"\n"
"Please note that hbactest executed with a trusted domain user as --user "
"parameter\n"
"can be only run by members of \"trust admins\" group.\n"
"\n"
"EXAMPLES:\n"
"\n"
"    1. Test if a user from a trusted domain specified by its shortname "
"matches any\n"
"       rule:\n"
"\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user 'DOMAIN\\Administrator' --host `hostname` --"
"service sshd\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"    Access granted: True\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"      Matched rules: allow_all\n"
"      Matched rules: can_login\n"
"\n"
"    2. Test if a user from a trusted domain specified by its domain name "
"matches\n"
"       any rule:\n"
"\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user 'Administrator@domain.com' --host `hostname` --"
"service sshd\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"    Access granted: True\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"      Matched rules: allow_all\n"
"      Matched rules: can_login\n"
"\n"
"    3. Test if a user from a trusted domain specified by its SID matches any "
"rule:\n"
"\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user S-1-5-21-3035198329-144811719-1378114514-500 \\\\\n"
"            --host `hostname` --service sshd\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"    Access granted: True\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"      Matched rules: allow_all\n"
"      Matched rules: can_login\n"
"\n"
"    4. Test if other user from a trusted domain specified by its SID matches "
"any rule:\n"
"\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user S-1-5-21-3035198329-144811719-1378114514-1203 \\"
"\\\n"
"            --host `hostname` --service sshd\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"    Access granted: True\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"      Matched rules: allow_all\n"
"      Not matched rules: can_login\n"
"\n"
"   5. Test if other user from a trusted domain specified by its shortname "
"matches\n"
"       any rule:\n"
"\n"
"    $ ipa hbactest --user 'DOMAIN\\Otheruser' --host `hostname` --service "
"sshd\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"    Access granted: True\n"
"    --------------------\n"
"      Matched rules: allow_all\n"
"      Not matched rules: can_login\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Simulera användning av värdbaserade\n"
"\n"
"åtkomstkontroller HBAC-regler styr vem som kan komma åt vilka\n"
"tjänster på vilka värdar. Du kan använda HBAC för att kontrollera vilka\n"
"användare eller grupper som kan få åtkomst\n"
"\n"
"till en tjänst eller en grupp av tjänster på en målvärd. Eftersom\n"
"tillämpningen av HBAC-regler innebär användning av en produktionsmiljö,\n"
"syftar detta insticksmodul till att simulera\n"
"\n"
"utvärderingen av HBAC-regler utan att ha åtkomst till\n"
"produktionsmiljön. Testa\n"
"\n"
"användare som kommer till en tjänst på en\n"
"namngiven värd mot befintliga aktiverade regler. ipa hbactest --user=\n"
"--host= --service= [--rules=rules-list]\n"
"\n"
"[--nodetail] [--enabled] [--disabled] [--sizelimit= ] --user, --host\n"
"\n"
"och --service är obligatoriska, övriga är valfria. Om --rules anges "
"simuleras\n"
"aktivering av de angivna reglerna och användarens\n"
"\n"
"inloggning testas med endast dessa regler. Om --enabled anges läggs alla "
"aktiverade\n"
"\n"
"HBAC-regler till simuleringen. Om --disabled anges läggs alla inaktiverade "
"HBAC-regler\n"
"\n"
"till simuleringen. Om --nodetail anges returneras ingen information om "
"regler som\n"
"\n"
"matchar/inte matchar. Om både --rules och --enabled anges, tillämpas "
"simuleringen\n"
"på --rules _och_ alla\n"
"\n"
"IPA-aktiverade regler. Om ingen --rules anges, körs simuleringen mot alla\n"
"IPA-aktiverade regler. Som standard finns det en IPA-omfattande begränsning "
"för antalet\n"
"hämtade poster, som du kan\n"
"\n"
"ändra med\n"
"\n"
"alternativet --sizelimit. EXEMPEL: 1. Använd alla aktiverade\n"
"HBAC-regler i IPA-databasen för att simulera: $ ipa hbactest\n"
"--user=a1a --host=bar\n"
"--service=sshd\n"
"-------------------- Åtkomst\n"
"beviljad: Sant -------------------- Regler\n"
"som inte matchas: my-second-rule Regler\n"
"som inte matchas: my-third-rule\n"
"Regler som inte matchas: myrule\n"
"\n"
"Regler som matchas: allow_all 2. Inaktivera detaljerad\n"
"sammanfattning av hur reglerna tillämpades: $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a\n"
"--host=bar --service=sshd\n"
"--nodetail --------------------\n"
"Åtkomst beviljad: Sant\n"
"\n"
"-------------------- 3. Testa uttryckligen\n"
"angivna HBAC-regler: $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar\n"
"--service=sshd \\\\ --rules=myrule --rules=my-second-rule\n"
"--------------------- Åtkomst\n"
"beviljad: False\n"
"--------------------- Regler\n"
"som inte matchar: my-second-rule Regler\n"
"som inte matchar: myrule 4. Använd\n"
"\n"
"alla aktiverade HBAC-regler i IPA-databasen + uttryckligen angivna regler: $ "
"ipa\n"
"hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd \\\\ --rules=myrule\n"
"--rules=my-second-rule --enabled -------------------- Åtkomst\n"
"beviljad: Sant\n"
"-------------------- Regler\n"
"som inte matchas:\n"
"min-andra-regel Regler som inte matchas:\n"
"min-tredje-regel Regler som inte matchas:\n"
"minregel Regler som matchas:\n"
"allow_all 5. Testa alla inaktiverade\n"
"\n"
"HBAC-regler i IPA-databasen: $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a\n"
"--host=bar --service=sshd --disabled --------------------- Åtkomst\n"
"beviljad: False\n"
"--------------------- Regler\n"
"som inte matchas: new-rule\n"
"6. Testa alla inaktiverade HBAC-regler\n"
"\n"
"i IPA-databasen + uttryckligen angivna regler: $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a --"
"host=bar\n"
"--service=sshd \\\\ --rules=myrule --rules=my-second-rule\n"
"--disabled --------------------- Tillgång beviljad: Falsk\n"
"--------------------- Regler\n"
"som inte matchar: my-second-rule\n"
"Regler som inte matchar:\n"
"my-third-rule Regler som inte matchar:\n"
"myrule 7. Testa alla (aktiverade och\n"
"inaktiverade) HBAC-regler i\n"
"\n"
"IPA-databasen: $ ipa hbactest --user=a1a --host=bar --service=sshd\n"
"\\\\ --enabled --disabled -------------------- Åtkomst beviljad:\n"
"Sant -------------------- Regler\n"
"som inte matchas:\n"
"min-andra-regel Regler som\n"
"inte matchas: min-tredje-regel\n"
"Regler som inte matchas: minregel Regler\n"
"som inte matchas: ny-regel Regler som\n"
"matchas: allow_all HBACTEST OCH\n"
"BETRODDA DOMÄNER När en extern\n"
"betrodd domän konfigureras i IPA\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"tillämpas HBAC-regler även på\n"
"\n"
"användare som får åtkomst till IPA-resurser från den betrodda domänen. "
"Användare\n"
"och grupper i betrodda domäner (och deras SID) kan sedan tilldelas externa "
"grupper\n"
"som kan vara medlemmar i POSIX-grupper i IPA, vilka kan användas i HBAC-"
"regler\n"
"och därmed ge åtkomst till resurser som skyddas av HBAC-systemet. hbactest-"
"insticksmodul\n"
"kan testa åtkomst för både lokala IPA-användare och\n"
"\n"
"användare från betrodda domäner, antingen med ett fullständigt användarnamn "
"eller\n"
"med användar-SID. Sådana användarnamn måste ha en betrodd domän angiven som "
"ett\n"
"kort namn (DOMAIN\\Administrator) eller med ett användarprincipnamn (UPN),\n"
"Administrator@ad.test. Observera att hbactest som körs med en användare från "
"en\n"
"\n"
"betrodd domän som --user-parameter endast kan köras av medlemmar i gruppen "
"\"trust\n"
"admins\". EXEMPEL: 1. Testa om en användare från en\n"
"\n"
"betrodd\n"
"\n"
"domän som anges med sitt kortnamn matchar någon regel: $ ipa hbactest --"
"user\n"
"'DOMAIN\\Administrator'\n"
"\n"
"--host `hostname` --service sshd -------------------- Åtkomst beviljad: "
"Sant\n"
"--------------------\n"
"Matchande regler: allow_all\n"
"Matchande regler: can_login\n"
"2. Testa om en användare från\n"
"en betrodd domän som anges med\n"
"\n"
"sitt domännamn matchar någon regel: $ ipa hbactest --user "
"'Administrator@domain.com'\n"
"--host `hostname`\n"
"\n"
"--service sshd -------------------- Tillgång beviljad: "
"Sant -------------------- Matchade\n"
"regler: allow_all Matchade\n"
"regler: can_login 3. Testa\n"
"om en användare från en\n"
"betrodd domän som anges av dess\n"
"SID matchar någon regel: $ ipa\n"
"\n"
"hbactest --user S-1-5-21-3035198329-144811719-1378114514-500 \\\\ --host "
"`hostname`\n"
"\n"
"--service sshd -------------------- Åtkomst beviljad: "
"Sant --------------------\n"
"Matchade regler: allow_all Matchade regler:\n"
"can_login 4. Testa om andra\n"
"användare från en betrodd\n"
"domän som anges av dess\n"
"SID matchar någon regel: $ ipa\n"
"hbactest --user\n"
"\n"
"S-1-5-21-3035198329-144811719-1378114514-1203 \\\\ --host `hostname` --"
"service sshd\n"
"\n"
"-------------------- Åtkomst beviljad: Sant -------------------- Matchade\n"
"regler: allow_all Icke matchade regler: can_login\n"
"5. Testa om andra användare\n"
"från en betrodd domän som\n"
"anges av dess kortnamn\n"
"matchar någon regel: $ ipa\n"
"hbactest --user 'DOMAIN\\Otheruser'\n"
"\n"
"--host `hostname` --service sshd -------------------- Åtkomst beviljad: "
"Sant\n"
"--------------------\n"
"\n"
"Matchade regler: allow_all Icke matchade regler: can_login\n"

